<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <%- include('../layouts/head', { title: title, seo: typeof seo !== 'undefined' ? seo : null }) %>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/static-pages.css">
  <script type="application/ld+json">{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is HelloRun?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "HelloRun is a running event platform for virtual, on-site, and hybrid events. Runners can register, submit proof, track review status, and access event recognition when enabled." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is a virtual run?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A virtual run is an event where you complete your activity from your own safe location within the event period, then submit activity proof for review." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Do I need a GPS watch?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "No. Use the tracking method accepted by the event. Many events accept screenshots from running apps, GPS watches, treadmill records, or manual entries when the rules allow them." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can I use Strava, Garmin, Nike Run Club, Huawei Health, Samsung Health, or other apps?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Usually yes if the event accepts app screenshots and your proof clearly shows the required details. Always check the event page before submitting." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can I walk instead of run?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Some events accept walking, hiking, or mixed activities. The event page lists accepted activity types and completion rules." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can I join from anywhere?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Virtual events are generally open from anywhere unless the organizer lists location, delivery, eligibility, or country restrictions." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can one activity count for multiple eligible events?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "HelloRun may allow one activity to be submitted to multiple eligible registrations when the activity falls within each event window and matches the rules. Organizers still review each submission separately." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What proof is accepted?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Accepted proof depends on the event. Common proof includes app screenshots, GPS activity records, treadmill screenshots, or manual entries with clear supporting details." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What should my screenshot show?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Your screenshot should show the activity date, distance, duration, and source app or device. If possible, include the activity type and name shown by the app." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Why does my result need review?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Review helps protect event credibility. Organizers may check dates, distance, names, duplicate submissions, proof clarity, and eligibility before approving results." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Why was my result rejected?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Common reasons include missing details, wrong event date, distance below the requirement, blurry proof, duplicate submission, or proof that does not match the account or event rules." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What if my app shows miles instead of kilometers?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Submit the clearest proof available and explain the unit if the event allows it. Organizers may convert the distance or ask for clearer evidence." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "When will my result appear?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Approved results may appear after organizer review, depending on leaderboard settings. Pending or rejected results may not be shown publicly." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "How are rankings calculated?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Rankings depend on the event setup. Some leaderboards rank fastest finishers, while accumulated challenges may rank verified total distance." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "How do certificates work?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Certificates become available only when the event enables certificates and your registration or result meets the event requirements." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What if my certificate has the wrong name?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Check your profile name and contact support or the organizer with the event name, confirmation code, and the correction needed." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can I create an event?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Organizer access depends on account status and platform review. Approved organizers can create and manage events through their dashboard." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What event types are supported?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "HelloRun supports virtual runs, on-site races, hybrid events, single-distance events, and accumulated distance challenges." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can schools or communities use HelloRun?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Schools, clubs, local groups, and community organizations can use HelloRun for wellness events, fundraising runs, and participation challenges when their setup fits the platform workflow." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can events be free or paid?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Events may be free or paid depending on the organizer configuration. Paid events can require payment receipt review before result submission unlocks." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is HelloRun free?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Creating an account may be free, but individual event fees depend on the organizer and event setup." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "How is my data handled?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "HelloRun uses account, registration, payment, and activity proof data to operate event workflows. Read the Privacy Policy and Data Usage Policy at hellorun.online/privacy for details." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "How do I contact support?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Use the Contact page at hellorun.online/contact and include your event name, confirmation code, account email, and a clear description of the concern." } }
  ]
}</script>
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('../layouts/nav') %>
  <main class="static-page">
    <div class="static-wrap">
      <header class="static-hero">
        <h1>FAQ</h1>
        <p>Answers to common questions from runners, walkers, event organizers, and community groups using HelloRun.</p>
      </header>

      <section class="faq-list">
        <h2>Runner Questions</h2>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>What is HelloRun?</h3>
          <p>HelloRun is a running event platform for virtual, on-site, and hybrid events. Runners can register, submit proof, track review status, and access event recognition when enabled.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>What is a virtual run?</h3>
          <p>A virtual run is an event where you complete your activity from your own safe location within the event period, then submit activity proof for review.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>Do I need a GPS watch?</h3>
          <p>No. Use the tracking method accepted by the event. Many events accept screenshots from running apps, GPS watches, treadmill records, or manual entries when the rules allow them.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can I use Strava, Garmin, Nike Run Club, Huawei Health, Samsung Health, or other apps?</h3>
          <p>Usually yes if the event accepts app screenshots and your proof clearly shows the required details. Always check the event page before submitting.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can I walk instead of run?</h3>
          <p>Some events accept walking, hiking, or mixed activities. The event page lists accepted activity types and completion rules.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can I join from anywhere?</h3>
          <p>Virtual events are generally open from anywhere unless the organizer lists location, delivery, eligibility, or country restrictions.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can one activity count for multiple eligible events?</h3>
          <p>HelloRun may allow one activity to be submitted to multiple eligible registrations when the activity falls within each event window and matches the rules. Organizers still review each submission separately.</p>
        </article>

        <h2>Proof Submission Questions</h2>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>What proof is accepted?</h3>
          <p>Accepted proof depends on the event. Common proof includes app screenshots, GPS activity records, treadmill screenshots, or manual entries with clear supporting details.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>What should my screenshot show?</h3>
          <p>Your screenshot should show the activity date, distance, duration, and source app or device. If possible, include the activity type and name shown by the app.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>Why does my result need review?</h3>
          <p>Review helps protect event credibility. Organizers may check dates, distance, names, duplicate submissions, proof clarity, and eligibility before approving results.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>Why was my result rejected?</h3>
          <p>Common reasons include missing details, wrong event date, distance below the requirement, blurry proof, duplicate submission, or proof that does not match the account or event rules.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>What if my app shows miles instead of kilometers?</h3>
          <p>Submit the clearest proof available and explain the unit if the event allows it. Organizers may convert the distance or ask for clearer evidence.</p>
        </article>

        <h2>Leaderboard and Certificate Questions</h2>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>When will my result appear?</h3>
          <p>Approved results may appear after organizer review, depending on leaderboard settings. Pending or rejected results may not be shown publicly.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>How are rankings calculated?</h3>
          <p>Rankings depend on the event setup. Some leaderboards rank fastest finishers, while accumulated challenges may rank verified total distance.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>How do certificates work?</h3>
          <p>Certificates become available only when the event enables certificates and your registration or result meets the event requirements.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>What if my certificate has the wrong name?</h3>
          <p>Check your profile name and contact support or the organizer with the event name, confirmation code, and the correction needed.</p>
        </article>

        <h2>Organizer Questions</h2>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can I create an event?</h3>
          <p>Organizer access depends on account status and platform review. Approved organizers can create and manage events through their dashboard.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>What event types are supported?</h3>
          <p>HelloRun supports virtual runs, on-site races, hybrid events, single-distance events, and accumulated distance challenges.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can schools or communities use HelloRun?</h3>
          <p>Yes. Schools, clubs, local groups, and community organizations can use HelloRun for wellness events, fundraising runs, and participation challenges when their setup fits the platform workflow.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can events be free or paid?</h3>
          <p>Events may be free or paid depending on the organizer configuration. Paid events can require payment receipt review before result submission unlocks.</p>
        </article>

        <h2>Account and Privacy Questions</h2>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>Is HelloRun free?</h3>
          <p>Creating an account may be free, but individual event fees depend on the organizer and event setup.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>How is my data handled?</h3>
          <p>HelloRun uses account, registration, payment, and activity proof data to operate event workflows. Read the <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> and <a href="/data-usage-policy">Data Usage Policy</a> for details.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="faq-item">
          <h3>How do I contact support?</h3>
          <p>Use the <a href="/contact">Contact</a> page and include your event name, confirmation code, account email, and a clear description of the concern.</p>
        </article>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <%- include('../layouts/footer') %>
  <script src="/js/main.js"></script>
  <script>
    (function initFaqPage() {
      if (window.lucide) lucide.createIcons();
    })();
  </script>
</body>
</html>
